{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to start with a story, a la Seth Godin,"},{"time":3000,"text":"from when I was 12 years old."},{"time":5000,"text":"My uncle Ed gave me a beautiful blue sweater --"},{"time":8000,"text":"at least I thought it was beautiful."},{"time":10000,"text":"And it had fuzzy zebras walking across the stomach,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and Mount Kilimanjaro and Mount Meru were kind of"},{"time":16000,"text":"right across the chest, that were also fuzzy."},{"time":18000,"text":"And I wore it whenever I could,"},{"time":19000,"text":"thinking it was the most fabulous thing I owned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"Until one day in ninth grade,"},{"time":24000,"text":"when I was standing with a number of the football players."},{"time":27000,"text":"And my body had clearly changed, and Matt,"},{"time":31000,"text":"who was undeniably my nemesis in high school,"},{"time":35000,"text":"said in a booming voice that"},{"time":36000,"text":"we no longer had to go far away to go on ski trips,"},{"time":40000,"text":"but we could all ski on Mount Novogratz."},{"time":42000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":43000,"text":"And I was so humiliated and mortified"},{"time":46000,"text":"that I immediately ran home to my mother and chastised her"},{"time":50000,"text":"for ever letting me wear the hideous sweater."},{"time":51000,"text":"We drove to the Goodwill and we threw the sweater away"},{"time":54000,"text":"somewhat ceremoniously,"},{"time":56000,"text":"my idea being that I would never have to think about the sweater"},{"time":59000,"text":"nor see it ever again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Fast forward -- 11 years later, I'm a 25-year-old kid."},{"time":64000,"text":"I'm working in Kigali, Rwanda, jogging through the steep slopes,"},{"time":71000,"text":"when I see, 10 feet in front of me, a little boy -- 11 years old --"},{"time":75000,"text":"running toward me, wearing my sweater."},{"time":78000,"text":"And I'm thinking, no, this is not possible."},{"time":80000,"text":"But so, curious, I run up to the child -- of course"},{"time":84000,"text":"scaring the living bejesus out of him --"},{"time":86000,"text":"grab him by the collar, turn it over, and there is my name"},{"time":89000,"text":"written on the collar of this sweater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"I tell that story, because it has served and continues to serve"},{"time":96000,"text":"as a metaphor to me about the level of connectedness"},{"time":100000,"text":"that we all have on this Earth."},{"time":102000,"text":"We so often don't realize what our action and our inaction"},{"time":106000,"text":"does to people we think we will never see and never know."},{"time":110000,"text":"I also tell it because it tells a larger contextual story"},{"time":113000,"text":"of what aid is and can be."},{"time":115000,"text":"That this traveled into the Goodwill in Virginia,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and moved its way into the larger industry,"},{"time":122000,"text":"which at that point was giving millions of tons of secondhand clothing to Africa and Asia."},{"time":126000,"text":"Which was a very good thing, providing low cost clothing."},{"time":130000,"text":"And at the same time, certainly in Rwanda,"},{"time":132000,"text":"it destroyed the local retailing industry."},{"time":134000,"text":"Not to say that it shouldn't have,"},{"time":136000,"text":"but that we have to get better at answering the questions"},{"time":139000,"text":"that need to be considered when we think about consequences"},{"time":142000,"text":"and responses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"So, I'm going to stick in Rwanda, circa 1985, 1986,"},{"time":149000,"text":"where I was doing two things."},{"time":150000,"text":"I had started a bakery with 20 unwed mothers."},{"time":153000,"text":"We were called the \"Bad News Bears,\" and our notion was"},{"time":155000,"text":"we were going to corner the snack food business in Kigali,"},{"time":158000,"text":"which was not hard because there were no snacks before us."},{"time":162000,"text":"And because we had a good business model, we actually did it,"},{"time":165000,"text":"and I watched these women transform on a micro-level."},{"time":167000,"text":"But at the same time, I started a micro-finance bank,"},{"time":170000,"text":"and tomorrow Iqbal Quadir is going to talk about Grameen,"},{"time":173000,"text":"which is the grandfather of all micro-finance banks,"},{"time":176000,"text":"which now is a worldwide movement -- you talk about a meme --"},{"time":179000,"text":"but then it was quite new, especially in an economy"},{"time":182000,"text":"that was moving from barter into trade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"We got a lot of things right."},{"time":187000,"text":"We focused on a business model; we insisted on skin in the game."},{"time":190000,"text":"The women made their own decisions at the end of the day"},{"time":193000,"text":"as to how they would use this access to credit"},{"time":195000,"text":"to build their little businesses, earn more income"},{"time":198000,"text":"so they could take care of their families better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"What we didn't understand, what was happening all around us,"},{"time":205000,"text":"with the confluence of fear, ethnic strife"},{"time":212000,"text":"and certainly an aid game, if you will, that was playing into"},{"time":217000,"text":"this invisible but certainly palpable movement inside Rwanda,"},{"time":223000,"text":"that at that time, 30 percent of the budget was all foreign aid."},{"time":226000,"text":"The genocide happened in 1994,"},{"time":228000,"text":"seven years after these women all worked together"},{"time":230000,"text":"to build this dream."},{"time":232000,"text":"And the good news was that the institution,"},{"time":234000,"text":"the banking institution, lasted."},{"time":236000,"text":"In fact, it became the largest rehabilitation lender in the country."},{"time":240000,"text":"The bakery was completely wiped out,"},{"time":242000,"text":"but the lessons for me were that accountability counts --"},{"time":247000,"text":"got to build things with people on the ground,"},{"time":249000,"text":"using business models where, as Steven Levitt would say,"},{"time":252000,"text":"the incentives matter."},{"time":254000,"text":"Understand, however complex we may be, incentives matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"So when Chris raised to me how wonderful everything"},{"time":262000,"text":"that was happening in the world,"},{"time":264000,"text":"that we were seeing a shift in zeitgeist,"},{"time":266000,"text":"on the one hand I absolutely agree with him,"},{"time":268000,"text":"and I was so thrilled to see what happened with the G8 --"},{"time":271000,"text":"that the world, because of people like Tony Blair and Bono"},{"time":275000,"text":"and Bob Geldof -- the world is talking about global poverty;"},{"time":279000,"text":"the world is talking about Africa"},{"time":281000,"text":"in ways I have never seen in my life."},{"time":283000,"text":"It's thrilling."},{"time":284000,"text":"And at the same time, what keeps me up at night"},{"time":287000,"text":"is a fear that we'll look at the victories of the G8 --"},{"time":291000,"text":"50 billion dollars in increased aid to Africa,"},{"time":294000,"text":"40 billion in reduced debt -- as the victory,"},{"time":297000,"text":"as more than chapter one, as our moral absolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"And in fact, what we need to do is see that as chapter one,"},{"time":305000,"text":"celebrate it, close it, and recognize that we need a chapter two"},{"time":309000,"text":"that is all about execution, all about the how-to."},{"time":312000,"text":"And if you remember one thing from what I want to talk about today,"},{"time":315000,"text":"it's that the only way to end poverty, to make it history,"},{"time":319000,"text":"is to build viable systems on the ground"},{"time":322000,"text":"that deliver critical and affordable goods and services to the poor,"},{"time":326000,"text":"in ways that are financially sustainable and scaleable."},{"time":329000,"text":"If we do that, we really can make poverty history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"And it was that -- that whole philosophy --"},{"time":335000,"text":"that encouraged me to start my current endeavor"},{"time":339000,"text":"called \"Acumen Fund,\""},{"time":341000,"text":"which is trying to build some mini-blueprints"},{"time":343000,"text":"for how we might do that in water, health and housing"},{"time":346000,"text":"in Pakistan, India, Kenya, Tanzania and Egypt."},{"time":349000,"text":"And I want to talk a little bit about that, and some of the examples,"},{"time":354000,"text":"so you can see what it is that we're doing."},{"time":356000,"text":"But before I do this -- and this is another one of my pet peeves --"},{"time":359000,"text":"I want to talk a little bit about who the poor are."},{"time":361000,"text":"Because we too often talk about them as these"},{"time":365000,"text":"strong, huge masses of people yearning to be free,"},{"time":368000,"text":"when in fact, it's quite an amazing story."},{"time":373000,"text":"On a macro level, four billion people on Earth make less than four dollars a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"That's who we talk about when we think about \"the poor.\""},{"time":380000,"text":"If you aggregate it, it's the third largest economy on Earth,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and yet most of these people go invisible."},{"time":386000,"text":"Where we typically work, there's people making between"},{"time":388000,"text":"one and three dollars a day."},{"time":390000,"text":"Who are these people?"},{"time":392000,"text":"They are farmers and factory workers."},{"time":395000,"text":"They work in government offices. They're drivers."},{"time":397000,"text":"They are domestics."},{"time":400000,"text":"They typically pay for critical goods and services like water,"},{"time":403000,"text":"like healthcare, like housing, and they pay 30 to 40 times"},{"time":407000,"text":"what their middleclass counterparts pay --"},{"time":409000,"text":"certainly where we work in Karachi and Nairobi."},{"time":413000,"text":"The poor also are willing to make, and do make, smart decisions,"},{"time":417000,"text":"if you give them that opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"So, two examples."},{"time":421000,"text":"One is in India, where there are 240 million farmers,"},{"time":424000,"text":"most of whom make less than two dollars a day."},{"time":426000,"text":"Where we work in Aurangabad, the land is extraordinarily parched."},{"time":430000,"text":"You see people on average making 60 cents to a dollar."},{"time":433000,"text":"This guy in pink is a social entrepreneur named Ami Tabar."},{"time":437000,"text":"What he did was see what was happening in Israel, larger approaches,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and figure out how to do a drip irrigation,"},{"time":443000,"text":"which is a way of bringing water directly to the plant stock."},{"time":448000,"text":"But previously it's only been created for large-scale farms,"},{"time":451000,"text":"so Ami Tabar took this and modularized it down to an eighth of an acre."},{"time":456000,"text":"A couple of principles:"},{"time":458000,"text":"build small."},{"time":460000,"text":"Make it infinitely expandable and affordable to the poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"This family, Sarita and her husband, bought a 15-dollar unit"},{"time":467000,"text":"when they were living in a -- literally a three-walled lean-to"},{"time":470000,"text":"with a corrugated iron roof."},{"time":473000,"text":"After one harvest, they had increased their income enough"},{"time":477000,"text":"to buy a second system to do their full quarter-acre."},{"time":480000,"text":"A couple of years later, I meet them."},{"time":482000,"text":"They now make four dollars a day, which is pretty much middle class for India,"},{"time":485000,"text":"and they showed me the concrete foundation they had just laid"},{"time":490000,"text":"to build their house."},{"time":491000,"text":"And I swear, you could see the future in that woman's eyes."},{"time":494000,"text":"Something I truly believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"You can't talk about poverty today without talking about malaria bed nets,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and I again give Jeffrey Sachs of Harvard"},{"time":502000,"text":"huge kudos for bringing to the world"},{"time":505000,"text":"this notion of his rage -- for five dollars you can save a life."},{"time":509000,"text":"Malaria is a disease that kills one to three million people a year."},{"time":513000,"text":"300 to 500 million cases are reported."},{"time":515000,"text":"It's estimated that Africa loses"},{"time":517000,"text":"about 13 billion dollars a year to the disease."},{"time":519000,"text":"Five dollars can save a life."},{"time":521000,"text":"We can send people to the moon; we can see if there's life on Mars --"},{"time":524000,"text":"why can't we get five-dollar nets to 500 million people?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"The question, though, is not \"Why can't we?\""},{"time":531000,"text":"The question is how can we help Africans do this for themselves?"},{"time":536000,"text":"A lot of hurdles."},{"time":537000,"text":"One: production is too low. Two: price is too high."},{"time":540000,"text":"Three: this is a good road in -- right near where our factory is located."},{"time":545000,"text":"Distribution is a nightmare, but not impossible."},{"time":548000,"text":"We started by making a 350,000-dollar loan"},{"time":552000,"text":"to the largest traditional bed net manufacturer in Africa"},{"time":554000,"text":"so that they could transfer technology from Japan"},{"time":559000,"text":"and build these long-lasting, five-year nets."},{"time":561000,"text":"Here are just some pictures of the factory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"Today, three years later, the company has employed"},{"time":566000,"text":"another thousand women."},{"time":569000,"text":"It contributes about 600,000 dollars in wages to the economy of Tanzania."},{"time":574000,"text":"It's the largest company in Tanzania."},{"time":576000,"text":"The throughput rate right now is 1.5 million nets,"},{"time":579000,"text":"three million by the end of the year."},{"time":581000,"text":"We hope to have seven million at the end of next year."},{"time":584000,"text":"So the production side is working."},{"time":586000,"text":"On the distribution side, though,"},{"time":587000,"text":"as a world, we have a lot of work to do."},{"time":589000,"text":"Right now, 95 percent of these nets are being bought by the U.N.,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and then given primarily to people around Africa."},{"time":597000,"text":"We're looking at building"},{"time":599000,"text":"on some of the most precious resources of Africa: people."},{"time":602000,"text":"Their women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":604000,"text":"And so I want you to meet Jacqueline,"},{"time":606000,"text":"my namesake, 21 years old."},{"time":608000,"text":"If she were born anywhere else but Tanzania,"},{"time":610000,"text":"I'm telling you, she could run Wall Street."},{"time":612000,"text":"She runs two of the lines, and has already saved enough money"},{"time":616000,"text":"to put a down payment on her house."},{"time":618000,"text":"She makes about two dollars a day, is creating an education fund,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and told me she is not marrying nor having children"},{"time":625000,"text":"until these things are completed."},{"time":628000,"text":"And so, when I told her about our idea --"},{"time":630000,"text":"that maybe we could take a Tupperware model from the United States,"},{"time":633000,"text":"and find a way for the women themselves to go out"},{"time":636000,"text":"and sell these nets to others --"},{"time":638000,"text":"she quickly started calculating what she herself could make"},{"time":641000,"text":"and signed up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"We took a lesson from IDEO, one of our favorite companies,"},{"time":648000,"text":"and quickly did a prototyping on this,"},{"time":650000,"text":"and took Jacqueline into the area where she lives."},{"time":653000,"text":"She brought 10 of the women with whom she interacts"},{"time":657000,"text":"together to see if she could sell these nets, five dollars apiece,"},{"time":659000,"text":"despite the fact that people say nobody will buy one,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and we learned a lot about how you sell things."},{"time":665000,"text":"Not coming in with our own notions,"},{"time":667000,"text":"because she didn't even talk about malaria until the very end."},{"time":669000,"text":"First, she talked about comfort, status, beauty."},{"time":672000,"text":"These nets, she said, you put them on the floor, bugs leave your house."},{"time":675000,"text":"Children can sleep through the night;"},{"time":677000,"text":"the house looks beautiful; you hang them in the window."},{"time":679000,"text":"And we've started making curtains,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and not only is it beautiful, but people can see status --"},{"time":685000,"text":"that you care about your children."},{"time":686000,"text":"Only then did she talk about saving your children's lives."},{"time":691000,"text":"A lot of lessons to be learned in terms of how we sell"},{"time":694000,"text":"goods and services to the poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"I want to end just by saying that there's enormous opportunity"},{"time":703000,"text":"to make poverty history."},{"time":705000,"text":"To do it right, we have to build business models that matter,"},{"time":708000,"text":"that are scaleable and that work with Africans, Indians,"},{"time":712000,"text":"people all over the developing world"},{"time":714000,"text":"who fit in this category, to do it themselves."},{"time":717000,"text":"Because at the end of the day, it's about engagement."},{"time":720000,"text":"It's about understanding that people really don't want handouts,"},{"time":723000,"text":"that they want to make their own decisions;"},{"time":725000,"text":"they want to solve their own problems;"},{"time":727000,"text":"and that by engaging with them,"},{"time":729000,"text":"not only do we create much more dignity for them,"},{"time":732000,"text":"but for us as well."},{"time":734000,"text":"And so I urge all of you to think next time"},{"time":737000,"text":"as to how to engage with this notion and this opportunity"},{"time":741000,"text":"that we all have -- to make poverty history --"},{"time":744000,"text":"by really becoming part of the process"},{"time":746000,"text":"and moving away from an us-and-them world,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and realizing that it's about all of us,"},{"time":750000,"text":"and the kind of world that we, together, want to live in and share."},{"time":753000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":754000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}